<p><em>Note: I’m trying to see if 914 can maintain equivalences of segmented inputs to which it knows the complete interaction and structure. –Intern Regal</em></p>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> One piece of paper containing binary code.<br />
<strong>Setting:</strong> 1:1<br />
<strong>Output:</strong> One piece of paper containing different binary code, assume to be the initial input of another Turing Machine.</p>
